# Normalise line endings. Without this, Git's core.autocrlf can check files out
# as CRLF on Windows, which makes `npm run lint` fail locally because Prettier's
# default `endOfLine: lf` flags those files — even though the Linux CI runner
# (which checks out LF) passes. Pinning eol=lf keeps local and CI in sync.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets: never normalise or diff their bytes.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.webp  binary
*.avif  binary
*.ico   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
*.otf   binary
*.eot   binary
*.pdf   binary
